---
description: Convert a markdown requirements plan into a GitHub Project backlog using the plan-to-project workflow.
alwaysApply: false
---

Use this rule when the user wants to turn a markdown requirements plan into a fully
structured GitHub Project backlog with Scope, Initiative, Epic, Story, and Task
hierarchy.

Key expectations:

- Follow the KDTIX markdown plan structure documented in:
  https://github.com/kdtix-open/skill-plan-to-project/blob/main/references/plan-format.md
- Use the workflow documented in:
  https://github.com/kdtix-open/skill-plan-to-project/blob/main/SKILL.md
- Preserve issue type hierarchy, parent-child relationships, blocker handling, and
  project field assignment.
- Prefer the repo's tested Python + `gh` CLI workflow over inventing an alternative.

Prerequisites to check before running the workflow:

- `gh auth status`
- Python 3.9+ available
- Target GitHub org has Issue Types configured: `Project Scope`, `Initiative`, `Epic`,
  `User Story`, `Task`
- Target GitHub Project V2 has fields: `Priority`, `Size`, and `Status`

When helping with this workflow:

1. Validate prerequisites first.
2. Parse the plan before creating issues.
3. Create issues top-down.
4. Set parent-child and blocker relationships.
5. Apply project fields and issue types.
6. Run compliance checks and review queue ordering.

If the user needs the exact commands or deeper implementation details, send them to
the source repo and workflow guide:

- https://github.com/kdtix-open/skill-plan-to-project
- https://skills.projectit.ai
